                            <comment id="14469358" author="blackdrag" created="Thu, 6 May 2010 09:00:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Since we don&apos;t use the class in the runtime itself and it is only for the purpose of others reading that information I suggest to make all initialization in the static initlizer. The boolean can be removed then and the read access to the properties should then be safe enough. Of course a write operation may still cause problems.&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Another way of &quot;fixing&quot; would be by documenting that this class is not thread safe and requires external synchronization.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14469345" author="roshandawrani" created="Thu, 6 May 2010 09:48:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Will the attached version do?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14469373" author="blackdrag" created="Fri, 7 May 2010 08:07:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;unless Peter thinks different I would say it should be good to go&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14469436" author="pniederw" created="Fri, 7 May 2010 08:31:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Looks good. Additionally, I&apos;d make all fields final.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14469316" author="roshandawrani" created="Fri, 7 May 2010 09:55:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Done. Thanks for the inputs, guys.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
